    {
      "name": "T-34/76",
      "size": 7,
      "loco": "tracked",
      "toughLevel": 1,
      "armourLevel": -2,
      "handlingLevel": -1,
      "desc": "Sloped armour, a powerful gun, and wide tracks that ate Russian mud for breakfast. The T-34 was the shock that broke the Wehrmacht's confidence — the first time German tankers met something their standard guns couldn't penetrate frontally.",
      "notes": "The T-34 changed tank warfare. Her sloped armour deflected shots that would penetrate a flat-faced Sherman, and she was simple enough to build in staggering numbers. The backbone of the Soviet armoured force and the benchmark for medium tank design. Heavy Armor, Sloped Armor (front), Tracked.",
      "weapons": [
        {
          "weaponId": "tank_gun_76mm",
          "mount": "turret",
          "linked": 0
        },
        {
          "weaponId": "mmg",
