    {
      "name": "T-72 MBT",
      "size": 9,
      "loco": "tracked",
      "toughLevel": 1,
      "armourLevel": 2,
      "speedLevel": 1,
      "desc": "The Soviet Union's answer to the Abrams — cheaper, simpler, and produced in staggering numbers. She's outclassed by Western tanks in one-on-one combat, but nobody fights one T-72. They fight fifty.",
      "notes": "The T-72 is the world's most exported tank. She shows up everywhere — every regional conflict, every arms deal, every third-world army. Not as capable as Western designs but available, affordable, and dangerous enough. Heavy Armor, Tracked.",
