    {
      "name": "T-80 MBT",
      "size": 8,
      "loco": "tracked",
      "toughLevel": 3,
      "armourLevel": 5,
      "desc": "The advanced Soviet tank that bridged the gap between the T-72 and Western designs. Reactive armour, a gas turbine engine, and an autoloaded 125mm gun. She was expensive by Soviet standards, which meant fewer were built.",
      "notes": "The T-80 is the Soviet answer to the Abrams — faster, lower-profile, and equipped with reactive armour. She represents the top tier of opposition for Cold War and modern campaigns. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.",
