      "desc": "The distinctive whumping rotor beat that defined a generation of warfare. She carries a squad into hot LZs, extracts the wounded under fire, and provides suppressive fire from the door guns. Thin-skinned and irreplaceable.",
      "notes": "The Huey is the sound of the Vietnam War. Her distinctive rotor beat tells everyone — friendly and hostile — that she's coming. She carries troops, she evacuates wounded, she provides fire support, and she defines the helicopter warfare era. Helicopter.",
